<BlogLayout
  title="Get Access to the Best Wedding Makeup Services"
  description="Five essential factors to consider when securing the best wedding makeup services for your big day."
  date="May 15, 2021"
  category="Bridal Beauty"
  image="/images/blog/best-wedding-makeup.jpg"
>
  <p class="text-lg text-grey leading-relaxed">
    Your wedding day makeup is about more than just looking beautiful — it's about feeling confident, radiant, and authentically yourself during one of the most important moments of your life. Here are five essential factors to help you find the best wedding makeup services.
  </p>

  <h2 class="text-display-sm font-serif italic text-charcoal mt-12 mb-4">1. Know Your Budget</h2>
  <p class="text-base text-grey leading-relaxed">
    Quality bridal makeup is an investment. Set a clear budget early in your planning process, but understand that the cheapest option isn't always the best value. Consider what's included — consultations, trials, travel, touch-up kits — and compare packages holistically.
  </p>

  <h2 class="text-display-sm font-serif italic text-charcoal mt-12 mb-4">2. Prioritize Hygiene</h2>
  <p class="text-base text-grey leading-relaxed">
    A professional makeup artist should maintain impeccable hygiene standards. Ask about their sanitization practices, product freshness, and whether they use disposable applicators. Your skin health and safety should never be compromised for aesthetics.
  </p>

  <h2 class="text-display-sm font-serif italic text-charcoal mt-12 mb-4">3. Share Your Vision</h2>
  <p class="text-base text-grey leading-relaxed">
    The best results come from clear communication. Create a mood board with reference images, discuss your dress and venue aesthetic, and be honest about your everyday makeup comfort level. A skilled artist will use your vision as a starting point and elevate it with their expertise.
  </p>

  <h2 class="text-display-sm font-serif italic text-charcoal mt-12 mb-4">4. Study Their Portfolio</h2>
  <p class="text-base text-grey leading-relaxed">
    Look beyond posed portfolio shots. Check for real wedding photography, candid moments, and how their work holds up in natural light. Consistency across different brides, skin types, and settings is the hallmark of a truly skilled professional.
  </p>

  <h2 class="text-display-sm font-serif italic text-charcoal mt-12 mb-4">5. Always Book a Trial</h2>
  <p class="text-base text-grey leading-relaxed">
    A trial appointment is non-negotiable. It's your opportunity to test products, refine the look, and build trust with your artist. Schedule it at least 2-4 weeks before the wedding, and take photos in different lighting to see how the makeup performs.
  </p>
</BlogLayout>
